#X text 33 222 The filter acts as a 'resonator' \, where it resonates at the resonant frequency for a period of time after the input signal has ceased., f 42;
#X text 31 27 The resonance parameter is specified by the decay time \, like the [resonant~] object., f 44;
#X obj 197 319 else/pulse~ 0.33 0.5;
#X text 358 406 If the attack time is the same as the decay time \, then the signal gets canceled out. If the attack time is greater than the decay time \, then the polarity of the impulse response is inverted.;
